description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Nurse Practitioner/Advanced Nurse Practitioner to join our dynamic, innovative and patient-focused practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a flexible, autonomous nurse practitioner/advanced nurse practitioner to work alongside our present clinical team in the support of daily urgent care and same day demand. The applicant will need to hold an independent nurse prescribing qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main duties would include Minor illness, telephone appointments, video calls, face 2 face when required and home visits on occasions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is negotiable, we are ideally looking for a minimum of 3 days a week, preferably 5 days.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is also being advertised on the Essex Primary Care Careers website – please complete only one application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have the right to close the advert earlier if we reach the maximum number of applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NO AGENCIES PLEASE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About The Candidate&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;As a key valued member of our nursing team :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be a Registered General Practice Nurse (currently registered with the NMC).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will hold a recognised ANP qualification at Masters level and work as an Independent Nurse Prescriber.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be able to work with a high degree of autonomy and be confident in leading in a variety of settings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your leadership of others will also enable you to use and further develop your teaching and mentoring experience/qualifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You will be forward thinking and strive to develop innovative ideas and new ways of working, that address the health needs of the practice, whilst motivating and encouraging others to do the same.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;As an excellent communicator and collaborator, you will embrace opportunities to work and liaise across multi-professional and agency boundaries in the interests of improving patient outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In addition to your highly developed clinical skills, your approach in the role will be consistently compassionate and respectful placing a high value on the dignity of patients, relatives, carers and colleagues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will have experience in diagnosing and treating patients who present with acute medical and minor illnesses and have relevant expertise in managing long term conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Experience in SystemOne would be preferred but training can be given)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;– High QOF achievers&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;– Clinical lead, ANP, 2 HCAs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;– Strong management and support structure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;– Regular in-practice teaching and support&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;– Approachable and friendly team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a small training practice, serving a patient population of&lt;em&gt; 6000&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate systemone&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;clinical system, with a history of 100% QOF achievement and a CQC rating of good&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;across all domains&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supporting your work life balance and professional development is important to us, so we will be happy to discuss any requirements for flexible working and offer the following benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Competitive salary based on experience&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Supportive and friendly environment&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Flexible working hours&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Peer support&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;CPD Support with training and development&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Extra pay for holiday cover&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;25 Days Holiday (pro Rata) + Bank Holidays&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;NHS Pension&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Study leave&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Free on-site parking&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Maternity pay&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
